  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Base Camp Lodge is offered on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Breakfast includes a classic continental offering with a variety of sweet and savoury options.</p>
<p>When you return from a day on the slopes, enjoy a three course evening meal served in the warm and welcoming dining area. </p>
<p>Christmas and New Years dinners are included. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Base Camp Lodge is in a great location in <a data-udi="umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28" href="/{localLink:umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28}" title="Les 2 Alpes">Les 2 Alpes</a> resort centre and just a few minutes walk from the ski lifts. After a day of exploring the slopes, the hotel also has a lovely south facing sun terrace and a sauna to soothe any achy ski legs.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>Located at the end of the main street of Les 2 Alpes, the Base Camp Lodge benefits from having convenient access to the slopes - the ski lifts are around 300 metres from the hotel, giving you access to the varied slopes suitable for all abilities. Off the slopes, the resort centre has a range of shops, bars and restaurants. Check out the '<a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/les-2-alpes#0" data-anchor="#0">Things to do</a>' tab on the main resort page for more inspiration. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>With skis and snowboards adoring the walls, quirky cable car lampshades and large windows overlooking the mountains, you can enjoy breakfast and evening meals in style. Serving comforting cuisine often including local products and Savoyard dishes, the social restaurant with banquet tables is the ideal spot to catch up with your family and friends. After a day on the slopes soak up some winter sun on the terrace with a drink and marvel at the mountain views on the south facing terrace, for more after ski entertainment live music and themed nights are often held throughout the winter season at the Lounge Bar.  </p>]]></description>
